						Sector
					

Accounting and public practice









Product Management Associate – Fund Solutions (Financial Services Sector)This is an exciting opportunity for a candidate (with knowledge of the FCA regulatory requirementsapplying to the regulated financial services firms in the UK) to join a very successful business in the Leeds area. The successful candidate will be a member of the Fund Solutions Product Management function, with the following responsibilities: Reviewing collective investment scheme (CIS) documentation: reviewing of Fund Solutions authorised schemes’ documentation on an annual basis to ensure that all documents are up-to-date, consistent and meet the regulatory requirements of the FCA’s COLL sourcebook; (This will entail close liaison with other internal stakeholders (such as the Transitions and Changes team, the Investment Management Supervision team, Legal Department and Compliance)).Depositary and FCA liaison: assist with the appropriate engagement with the relevant trustee / depositary and the FCA (all under supervision) on changes to documents, specifically full and simplified prospectus, requiring notification to, or approval by, the FCA.Changes to UK-authorised CISs:assist (under supervision) with proposals for changes to UK-authorised collective investment schemes (CISs) via the appropriate regulatory route under the FCA rules.Collective investment scheme wind-ups / terminations:Assist (under supervision) with ensuring that CIS’s that are required to be wound-up or terminated are undertaken within the requirements of the FCA’s Collective Investment Schemes COLL Sourcebook.Collation of monthly Board report:Assist with the collation of the Fund Solutions monthly report and other reports following approval and sign-off by senior management.Working within a small team you will:·Assist with the prospectus review of scheme documentation (full and simplified prospectus, key investor information document, instrument of incorporation / trust deed) to ensure that the companies’ prospectuses, simplified prospectuses, key investor information documents are in line with FCA requirements.·Engagement (under supervision) with the FCA and trustee / depositary on all matters relating to the companies’ prospectuses and simplified prospectuses – this will include regular reviews and amendments.·Track and report on progress of prospectus approval matters with FCA and depositary.·Ensure documentationand team procedures are maintained to a satisfactory standard.·Each member of staff has responsibility to adhere to the companies’ policies and procedures, in particular to ensure operational controls are carried out in accordance with laid down procedures, to ensure the ongoing mitigation of business risk. As an employee of our client you will be expected to be fully aware of Fund Solutions’ requirements for personal compliance - In particular requirements on personal account dealing, requirements on disclosure of gifts and benefits received and given, ensure any complaint that is justified or otherwise, is properly reported for adjudication in accordance with Fund Solutions procedures. Also ensuring that any incident which may involve a breach of money laundering rules is notified without delay to the Money Laundering Reporting Officer and ensure that personal data, however obtained, is properly protected in accordance with the requirements of the Data Protection Act and understand and conform to Fund Solutions’ requirements on Treating Customers Fairly.The successful candidate will have GCSE Grade C in Maths & English, knowledge of the FCA regulatory requirements applying to regulated financial services firms in the UK, the ability to work to deadlines and to be able to deal with high volumes of work. You will also have excellent interpersonal skills as you will be liaising with internal and external stakeholders. Legal skills would be helpful for reviewing documents and maintenance of policies to FCA rules. Please Note:When applying for a position online, please understand that whilst we review all CVs and applications that are sent to us, due to the large volume that we receive on a regular basis, we can only respond to those candidates that have been successful with their application. As such, if you do not hear from us within 14 working days, please accept that your application has been unsuccessful. We apologise for any inconvenience that this may cause. THE Agency (Recruitment) Limited.   This job was originally posted as www.totaljobs.com/job/75122955
					





